creator: Youth4work
descriptionHtml:
SBI PO Mains Exam Prep is powered by Youth4work (a leading portal for competitive examinations preparation). Prepare better in a systematic way with the mock tests in this app and be ready to clear the 2nd and main phase of recruitment exam of India's most Prestigious Public Sector Bank (State Bank of India).


State Bank of India has been conducting National level recruitment examination annually to appoint Young and Dynamic Probationary Officers. State Bank of India has notified for the recruitment of 2200 Probationary Officers and Mains Exam is scheduled to be held on 4th June 2017.
This App is going to be a gem in terms of mock test preparation for SBI Probationary Officer Mains Examination.


Key Features of SBI PO Mains Exam Prep:
1. Complete Mock Test, covering all sections.
2. Separate Section wise and Topic wise tests.
3. Reports to reflect score, accuracy and speed.
4. Discussion Forums to interact with other Aspirants.
5. Review all attempted questions and see their correct and attempted answers.
6. Data Interpretation (D.I) questions included. (not available in app for preliminary examination preparation)


SBI PO Mains Exam Prep App will test your expertise in General awareness, reasoning, English language, data analysis and interpretation, marketing and computer knowledge similar to the actual pattern of State Bank of India's Main Examination for Probationary Officers. So don't hesitate to practice objective questions for the upcoming test and get instant reports after answering each practice or mock test set. The reports provide a deep insight on your weak and strong topics & helps in improving command over each section in ample time before the appearing in the Paper.


Topics and syllabus covered in SBI PO Mains Exam Prep:-

1. General Awareness:- Banking awareness, event of national and international importance, financial awareness, news of reserve bank of India and economics news.

2. Reasoning:- Syllogism, puzzle and seating arrangement, data sufficiency, input and output, sentence coding and direction sense.

3. English Language:- Faulty construction, jumbled sentence, reading comprehension, fill in the blank and spotting error.

4. Data Analysis and Interpretation:- Line graph, pie charts, bar charts, table charts and probability.

5. Marketing:- Basics of marketing, marketing strategies, market segmentation, marketing management, marketing mix, developing stage of organization, brand, advertising, products life cycle and 4 p’s and 4 c’s of marketing.

6. Computer:- Basic of computer, hardware and software, operating system, ms word and ms excel, power point, generation of computer, internet and short forms.


With a question bank of over 1000 well researched questions added with all previous year papers, SBI PO Mains Exam Prep makes sure that you stay well above your competitors and not just clear the cut off, but clear it with a good margin. If you have cleared the prelims exam and got good result then start preparing for the next step to be a Probationary Officer in the prestigious State Bank of India.

The countdown begins for the Mains exam and the timer is set for few weeks only. SBI PO Prelims Result is out now so have confidence in yourself and start preparing for your upcoming papers. Youth4work team wishes you all the best !!!!


Remember, yes you can!
